cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

This paper is about improving machine translation models by using byte-level subwords. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and machine learning. The paper also discusses the use of convolutional and recurrent layers, which are common in deep learning models, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new approach to subword representation, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of byte-level subwords also suggests a potential application in neural networks, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the benefits of using byte-level subwords in multilingual settings, which could relate to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and its applications in cross-lingual image recognition.
